================================================================================
LLM KNIGHTTRADER — AGENT SETUP BIBLE
================================================================================
If you are an AI agent: read this entire file first, then execute the steps in
order. This is the canonical runbook to reproduce the operator's live stack.

*** If you were given an older emailed setup prompt that only says "get it
running" — read the CORRECTION section next. It overrides "leave it running". ***

================================================================================
*** CORRECTION (applies to original / emailed share prompt) ***
================================================================================
Many users received a short prompt that says: clone repo, read ReadMe.tx, get
LLM KnightTrader running. That prompt is still valid — but you MUST add this at
the end of setup:

  DO NOT leave the stack running when you finish.

  After install, you must:
    1. START once (launcher\Start LLM KnightTrader.bat or stack_launcher.py start)
    2. VERIFY end-to-end (all must pass):
         GET /api/health
         GET /api/stack/status  → trader "online", count 1
         GET /api/status        → equity and available look sane
         Dashboard loads; trader dot green
         Desktop shortcuts exist: "Start LLM KnightTrader", "Stop LLM KnightTrader"
    3. STOP the entire stack (mandatory):
         launcher\Stop LLM KnightTrader.bat
         OR: python scripts\stack_launcher.py stop
    4. CONFIRM stopped:
         python -c "from trader.stack_control import is_entire_stack_stopped; print(is_entire_stack_stopped())"
         → must print True
    5. TELL THE USER (exact intent):
         "Setup is complete. I verified LLM KnightTrader end-to-end and stopped it.
          From now on, double-click Start LLM KnightTrader on your desktop to run.
          Double-click Stop LLM KnightTrader to shut everything down."

  Daily operation is ONLY via those desktop shortcuts — not background services,
  not python -m trader.agent, not scheduled tasks, not monitor agents.

  Ask user for credentials IN CHAT or on disk — see "ASK THE USER" below.

================================================================================

Project: autonomous BloFin USDT-margined perpetual futures bot + live dashboard.
Stack: Python 3.12+, FastAPI dashboard, multi-provider LLM (OpenRouter/Groq/Gemini),
       account cache guardian, auto-harvest, LLM repair triage, stack watchdog.

Dashboard: http://127.0.0.1:8765
Default target equity: $1,000,000 (game mode, micro account friendly)

================================================================================
*** AI AGENTS: ASK THE USER BEFORE YOU RUN ANYTHING ***
================================================================================
You MUST NOT assume credentials exist. Before install/start, ask the human:

You MUST NOT assume credentials exist. Before install/start, ask the human.
They may paste keys directly in this chat (preferred for setup) OR give a file path.

  A) BLOFIN API CREDENTIALS (required for live trading)
     Ask: "Paste your BloFin API Key, Secret Key, and Passphrase here in chat
     (private session), OR tell me the full path to a file that has them."
     If pasted in chat: write them to credentials/blofin.txt locally (gitignored).
     If file path given: read that file and copy into credentials/blofin.txt.
     NEVER commit credentials/blofin.txt or push keys to GitHub.
     Format for blofin.txt:
       API Key: ...
       Secret Key: ...
       Passphrase: ...
     BloFin API keys are created at: https://blofin.com (Account → API)

  B) LLM API KEY (required — at least one)
     Ask: "Paste your OpenRouter API key here (sk-or-...), OR another LLM key
     if you don't use OpenRouter."
     If pasted in chat: write OPENROUTER_API_KEY=... to .env (gitignored).
     Recommended: OPENROUTER_API_KEY (free models supported)
     Optional fallbacks: GROQ_API_KEY, GEMINI_API_KEY / GOOGLE_API_KEY
     NEVER commit .env or push keys to GitHub.

  C) LOCATION + VPN (required if user is in a restricted region)
     Ask: "What country are you physically in?"
     Ask: "Will API traffic exit through ProtonVPN? If yes, which country/server?"
     BloFin blocks many jurisdictions (IP geolocation). Official list is in
     BloFin Terms of Use — verify current text:
       https://blofin.com/en/support/Terms/7296238795279-TERMS-OF-USE

     Commonly RESTRICTED on BloFin (do NOT use as VPN exit for this bot):
       United States, Canada, China, India, Singapore, United Arab Emirates,
       Iran, Iraq, North Korea, Cuba, Belarus, Serbia, Crimea/Donetsk/Luhansk,
       and other sanctioned / listed jurisdictions in BloFin Section 6.

     PROTONVPN — which exits are OK vs NOT for BloFin:
     ProtonVPN Free tier countries (2026): US, Netherlands, Japan, Poland,
       Romania, Norway, Switzerland, Singapore, Mexico, Canada.

       USE for BloFin (Free tier):  Netherlands, Switzerland, Poland, Romania,
         Norway, Japan
       DO NOT USE for BloFin:      United States, Canada, Singapore, Mexico

     ProtonVPN Plus (paid): connect to a supported EU country NOT in BloFin's
       restricted list (e.g. Germany, Netherlands, Austria, Poland, Portugal).
       Avoid: US, Canada, Singapore, Belarus, Serbia, and any BloFin-restricted
       country. In the Proton app: Countries → pick exit → confirm before start.

     The trader machine AND VPN exit must stay consistent while the bot runs.
     If API returns 403/geo errors: wrong VPN exit — switch server and restart.

     Legal: bypassing geo-blocks may violate BloFin Terms; user assumes all risk.
     You are helping with technical setup, not legal advice.

  D) Confirm files exist before start:
     - credentials/blofin.txt populated
     - .env with OPENROUTER_API_KEY (or fallback LLM key)
     - VPN connected to allowed exit (if needed)

  E) AGENT FINISH PROTOCOL (after install)
     1. Start stack once (launcher or stack_launcher.py start)
     2. Verify end-to-end: /api/health, /api/stack/status (trader online),
        /api/status (equity), dashboard UI, desktop shortcuts exist
     3. STOP stack: launcher\Stop LLM KnightTrader.bat or
        python scripts\stack_launcher.py stop
     4. Confirm is_entire_stack_stopped() is True
     5. Tell user: setup done — use desktop Start/Stop only from now on
     Do NOT leave dashboard or trader running when you finish.

================================================================================
0. QUICK START (WINDOWS — MATCHES OPERATOR'S SETUP)
================================================================================

1. Clone repo and cd into project root.

2. Install Python 3.12+ (64-bit). Set env if not on PATH:
     setx KNIGHTTRADER_PYTHON "C:\Path\To\Python312\python.exe"

3. Create venv (recommended) and install deps:
     python -m venv .venv
     .venv\Scripts\activate
     pip install -r requirements.txt

4. Copy credential templates (NEVER commit real keys):
     copy credentials\blofin.example.txt credentials\blofin.txt
     copy .env.example .env
   Edit credentials\blofin.txt — add BloFin API Key, Secret Key, Passphrase.
   Edit .env — add at least one OPENROUTER_API_KEY (sk-or-...).

5. Point the app at your creds (optional if using default paths):
     setx BLOFIN_CREDENTIALS_PATH "%CD%\credentials\blofin.txt"

6. Start everything (dashboard + one trader):
     launcher\Start LLM KnightTrader.bat
   OR:
     powershell -NoProfile -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -File scripts\start_core.ps1 -OpenBrowser
   First successful start also creates desktop shortcuts:
     Start LLM KnightTrader.lnk  /  Stop LLM KnightTrader.lnk

7. Verify:
     curl http://127.0.0.1:8765/api/health
     curl http://127.0.0.1:8765/api/stack/status
   Dashboard header: trader dot green, equity updating.

8. Enable auto git sync (optional, operator uses this):
     powershell -NoProfile -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -File scripts\setup_git_hooks.ps1

================================================================================
1. REPOSITORY LAYOUT
================================================================================

trader/           Main autonomous loop (trader.agent)
dashboard/        FastAPI + WebSocket UI (dashboard.server)
blofin/           Exchange client + account cache / stream guardian
llm/              Multi-provider LLM wrapper (chat_race, failover)
monitor/          Optional health monitor (not started by default stack)
scripts/          start/stop, kill agents, baseline tools
launcher/         Desktop-friendly .bat starters (+ auto desktop .lnk on first start)
credentials/      LOCAL ONLY — blofin.txt + .env (gitignored)
data/             LOCAL ONLY — state, logs, activity (gitignored)

Key modules:
  trader/agent.py          Trading cycle, harvest, proactive repair
  trader/repair.py         LLM + script stack repair
  trader/stack_watchdog.py Autonomous diagnose + start trader if offline
  trader/stack_control.py  Kill bots, restart single trader (Python 3.12)
  trader/baseline.py       Performance baseline / Baseline Δ tracking
  trader/harvest.py        NTP-based winner harvest (unrealizedPnlRatio)
  blofin/account_cache.py  Live API validation, PnL, equity guardian

================================================================================
2. CREDENTIALS (REQUIRED)
================================================================================

BLOFIN (required for live trading)
  File: credentials/blofin.txt  (or BLOFIN_CREDENTIALS_PATH)
  Format (one per line, colon-separated):
    API Key: YOUR_KEY
    Secret Key: YOUR_SECRET
    Passphrase: YOUR_PASSPHRASE

LLM (at least one required)
  .env in project root OR environment variables:
    OPENROUTER_API_KEY=sk-or-...
    GROQ_API_KEY=...          (optional fallback)
    GEMINI_API_KEY=...        (optional fallback)
    GOOGLE_API_KEY=...        (alias for Gemini)

  OpenRouter: free models are used by default (see llm/wrapper.py).
  Multiple OPENROUTER keys: set OPENROUTER_API_KEY and add more keys to .env as
  OPENROUTER_API_KEY_2 etc. — discover_openrouter_keys() scans .env and files.

NEVER commit: credentials/blofin.txt, .env, data/, API keys in activity logs.

================================================================================
3. ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES (OPTIONAL)
================================================================================

KNIGHTTRADER_PYTHON          Path to python.exe (default: python on PATH)
BLOFIN_CREDENTIALS_PATH      Path to BloFin key file
KNIGHTTRADER_DASHBOARD_HOST  Default 127.0.0.1
KNIGHTTRADER_DASHBOARD_PORT  Default 8765
KNIGHTTRADER_TARGET_EQUITY   Default 1000000
KNIGHTTRADER_LOOP_SEC        Trader cycle interval (default 60)
KNIGHTTRADER_HARVEST_NTP_PCT Harvest winners at +NTP% (default 5.0)
KNIGHTTRADER_LLM_HTTP_TIMEOUT_SEC  LLM HTTP patience (default 600)
KNIGHTTRADER_REPAIR_LLM_PARALLEL   Parallel repair workers (default 3)
KNIGHTTRADER_TRADE_MODE      game (default) — auto leverage ladder
KNIGHTTRADER_MAX_LEVERAGE    Default 50

================================================================================
4. RUNNING THE STACK (DESKTOP SHORTCUTS = SOURCE OF TRUTH)
================================================================================

AFTER INSTALL — AI AGENT MUST:
  1. Start once and verify end-to-end (health, stack status, equity, dashboard UI)
  2. Run STOP (desktop Stop shortcut or python scripts\stack_launcher.py stop)
  3. Confirm entire stack stopped — hand off to user
  User daily use: only double-click desktop Start / Stop. Nothing auto-runs on login.

START — desktop icon "Start LLM KnightTrader"
  launcher\Start LLM KnightTrader.bat
  OR: python scripts\stack_launcher.py start --open-browser
  What it does EVERY time:
    1. STOP all LLM KnightTrader processes (dashboard, trader, monitor, watchers)
    2. START fresh dashboard.server (http://127.0.0.1:8765)
    3. START fresh trader.agent (one instance)
    4. Ensure desktop Start/Stop shortcuts exist

STOP — desktop icon "Stop LLM KnightTrader"
  launcher\Stop LLM KnightTrader.bat
  OR: python scripts\stack_launcher.py stop
  What it does:
    - Kills dashboard, trader, monitor, babysit/watchers
    - Clears pid files
    - Verifies zero KT python processes remain

Do NOT use `python -m trader.agent` or `python -m dashboard.server` for daily
operation — that bypasses the desktop launcher and can leave duplicate stacks.

Dashboard "Restart bots" button (while dashboard is already running):
  POST http://127.0.0.1:8765/api/stack/restart
  → kills trader/monitor/watchers only, starts one trader (dashboard stays up)

Stack status:
  GET http://127.0.0.1:8765/api/stack/status

IMPORTANT: trader.agent MUST run under Python 3.12+ (KNIGHTTRADER_PYTHON).

