5. DASHBOARD FEATURES
================================================================================

URL: http://127.0.0.1:8765

- Live equity, available, unrealized PnL (WebSocket + API guardian)
- Baseline Δ — click metric to set baseline to current equity or custom $
- Chat with LLM KnightTrader (instructions wired to trader loop)
- Stack status + "Restart bots" button
- Activity log, positions, trades, last LLM decision

Chat commands:
  "set baseline" / "reset baseline"     → lock baseline at current equity
  "set baseline to 3.75"                → lock at specific $

API:
  GET  /api/status
  GET  /api/account
  GET  /api/stack/status
  POST /api/stack/restart
  POST /api/stack/repair
  POST /api/baseline/set   {"use_current": true} or {"equity": 3.29}
  POST /api/chat           {"message": "..."}

================================================================================
6. ARCHITECTURE (HOW IT BEHAVES LIVE)
================================================================================

Trader loop (every KNIGHTTRADER_LOOP_SEC):
  1. Refresh account (cache + live API guardian)
  2. repair_stack — kill duplicate traders, triage errors
  3. Auto-harvest winners at +NTP% (margin ROI, not price %)
  4. Proactive repairs on harvest gaps / LLM-flagged anomalies
  5. LLM decision (chat_race across providers) → execute trades
  6. Learn from cycle, snapshot baseline progress

Dashboard background:
  - Account stream guardian (~3s): compare display vs live BloFin
  - Stack watchdog (~30s): trader offline → start_single_trader()
  - Activity WebSocket to UI

Repair policy (trader/repair.py):
  - Script first (deterministic playbooks)
  - Repair LLM for novel issues (trade failures, bugs, harvest gaps)
  - No short timeouts — parallel LLM workers race until response
  - Known maintenance (stale cache) stays script-only

NTP / harvest:
  position_ntp_pct = unrealizedPnlRatio * 100  (exchange field)
  Harvest when NTP >= KNIGHTTRADER_HARVEST_NTP_PCT (default 5%)

================================================================================
7. TROUBLESHOOTING
================================================================================

Trader offline / exits immediately:
  - Check data\logs\trader.err
  - python -m trader.agent   (run foreground to see traceback)
  - Dashboard stack watchdog should auto-start; verify stack_control.py

Equity / available wrong on dashboard:
  - Guardian refreshes from live API; wait ~8s
  - POST /api/stack/repair or restart trader

"Repair LLM" loops:
  - Should be fixed: noise filtered, no 25s timeout
  - Check activity.jsonl for phase=stack_watchdog vs trader_offline

Rate limited (BloFin 403):
  - Bot waits and uses cache; do not hammer API

LLM all providers failed:
  - Verify OPENROUTER_API_KEY in .env
  - llm.wait_for_provider blocks until cooldown clears

Duplicate traders:
  - Click Restart bots on dashboard
  - python scripts\kill_agents.py

================================================================================
8. DEVELOPMENT & GIT AUTO-SYNC
================================================================================

Setup once after clone:
  powershell -File scripts\setup_git_hooks.ps1

This enables:
  - .githooks/post-commit → git push after every commit
  - .cursor/hooks (stop) → auto commit + push when Cursor agent finishes

Manual sync:
  powershell -File scripts\auto_sync_git.ps1 -Message "describe change"

Public repo: https://github.com/1bananaonthewall-ux/llm-knighttrader
Share prompt for new users/agents: SHARE_PROMPT.txt (copy-paste to any AI)
(If forked, update remote URL in your clone.)

